### .gitignore

Create a new file in your project's root folder named `.gitignore` (note the leading dot) and paste the following content into it. This will prevent your secrets and local work files from ever being uploaded to GitHub.

```gitignore
# This file tells Git which files and folders to ignore.

# Local Configuration
# This file contains secret API keys and should never be committed.
config.js

# Workshop Folder
# For work-in-progress graphics and other temporary assets.
/workshop/

# Build output
/dist/
/build/

# Node.js dependencies
/node_modules/

# Log files
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Editor-specific files
.idea/
.vscode/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# Operating System files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db